Document: NavigationRegion3D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationregion3d.rst
Summary: Defines a navigation region in 3D space for pathfinding.
NavigationRegion3D

Inherits: Node3D < CanvasItem < Node < Object

A navigation region in 3D space.

This node is used to define a navigation area in your scene. It can be used to bake navigation meshes for pathfinding. The navigation region is defined by its geometry, which can be provided by a NavigationMesh resource.

Properties:
navigation_mesh (NavigationMesh): The NavigationMesh resource used by this region.
See also: NavigationMesh.

Enabled:
navigation_mesh_dirty (bool): If true, the navigation mesh needs to be baked.
Key Rule: Setting this to true forces a bake.

bake_navigation_mesh()
Bakes the navigation mesh for this region.

get_navigation_mesh()
Returns the NavigationMesh resource used by this region.

set_navigation_mesh(navigation_mesh: NavigationMesh)
Sets the NavigationMesh resource used by this region.
