Document: NavigationRegion3D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationregion3d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the NavigationRegion3D node, which defines a navigation area for pathfinding.

Property: enabled (bool)
Default: true
Setter: set_enabled(value: bool)
Getter: is_enabled() -> bool
Determines if the NavigationRegion3D is enabled or disabled.

Property: enter_cost (float)
Default: 0.0
Setter: set_enter_cost(value: float)
Getter: get_enter_cost() -> float
When pathfinding enters this region's navigation mesh from another region's navigation mesh, the enter_cost value is added to the path distance for determining the shortest path.

Property: navigation_layers (int)
Default: 1
Setter: set_navigation_layers(value: int)
Getter: get_navigation_layers() -> int
A bitfield determining all navigation layers the region belongs to. These navigation layers can be checked upon when requesting a path with NavigationServer3D.map_get_path().

Property: navigation_mesh (NavigationMesh)
Setter: set_navigation_mesh(value: NavigationMesh)
Getter: get_navigation_mesh() -> NavigationMesh
The NavigationMesh resource to use.

Property: travel_cost (float)
Default: 1.0
Setter: set_travel_cost(value: float)
Getter: get_travel_cost() -> float
When pathfinding moves inside this region's navigation mesh, the traveled distances are multiplied with travel_cost for determining the shortest path.

Property: use_edge_connections (bool)
Default: true
Setter: set_use_edge_connections(value: bool)
Getter: get_use_edge_connections() -> bool
If enabled, the navigation region will use edge connections to connect with other navigation regions within proximity of the navigation map edge connection margin.
